alert.note: Alert for Annette Island; Ketchikan Gateway Borough; Prince of Wales Island (Alaska) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 12 at 4:16AM AKST until December 12 at 9:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 9 PM AKST THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Southeast winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 60 mph expected. * WHERE...Prince of Wales Island, Ketchikan Gateway Borough and Annette Island. * WHEN...From noon to 9 PM AKST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...High winds will blow around unsecured objects and may damage property and cause power outages. Travel will be difficult. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong wind gusts up to 50 mph are expected to continue through Tuesday morning with the passing of the initial front with gusts near or greater than 60 mph mainly after noon. A shift of wind to the southwest is expected late Tuesday night.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure vessels and loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind. Report any damage to the National Weather Service by visiting weather.gov/Juneau/StormReports
